(LAP System Permission-Based Module Workflows) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Login and permissions) Tj
T*
(1. Admin or Superadmin creates an employee in LAP.) Tj
T*
(2. Admin grants per-employee permissions from Permission Manager.) Tj
T*
(3. Employee logs in and receives permission codes in the JWT/auth state.) Tj
T*
(4. Sidebar and module screens show only workflows allowed by those codes.) Tj
T*
(5. Backend APIs also check the same permission codes, so hidden UI is not the only protectio) Tj
T*
(n.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Admin and Superadmin) Tj
T*
(- Full access by role.) Tj
T*
(- Can see all modules and all protected workflows.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Managers, HR, Employees) Tj
T*
(- See only explicitly granted UserPermissionOverride permissions.) Tj
T*
(- Example: view_tasks shows own task dashboard and my tasks only.) Tj
T*
(- Example: create_task shows create task workflow but not full team task board unless view_t) Tj
T*
(eam_tasks or assign_task is also granted.) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
